  <p><strong>After Aunt Deb's funeral, something shifted.</strong></p>

  <p>I was already in pharmacy school. But now I had a reason that went beyond the textbook.</p>

  <p>I wasn't going to stand behind a counter and staple bags. I was going to figure out <em>why this kept happening</em>, and what could actually be done about it.</p>

  <p><strong>I became a pharmacist because three women I loved couldn't breathe.</strong></p>

  <p>For the next decade, I worked directly with smokers and vapers. I helped people quit. Guided them through relapses. Celebrated the ones who stuck with it.</p>

  <p>But here's the thing nobody warned me about, the thing I kept seeing over and over again:</p>

  <div class="prl-pull-quote">People would quit smoking… and still couldn't breathe.</div>

  <div class="prl-divider"></div>

  <!-- ═══ SECTION 3: THE UNCOMFORTABLE TRUTH ═══ -->
  <div class="prl-section-label-wrap">
    <span class="prl-section-badge">02</span>
    <span class="prl-section-label-text">The Uncomfortable Truth</span>
  </div>

  <p>Let me be blunt about something most people don't want to hear.</p>

  <p><strong>Quitting is only half the battle.</strong></p>

  <p>Your lungs don't just spring back because you threw out your last pack. After years, sometimes decades, of filtering tar, chemicals, and toxins, the damage sits there.</p>

  <p>The mucus is still trapped. The tiny cleaning hairs in your airways (called cilia) are still flattened. The inflammation is still simmering.</p>

  <p><strong>That's why you still:</strong></p>

  <div class="prl-symptom-box">
    <div class="prl-symptom-item"><span class="prl-symptom-check">✔</span><span>Wake up every morning with that wet, rattling cough.</span></div>
    <div class="prl-symptom-item"><span class="prl-symptom-check">✔</span><span>Get winded walking up a flight of stairs.</span></div>
    <div class="prl-symptom-item"><span class="prl-symptom-check">✔</span><span>Feel a tightness in your chest that never fully goes away.</span></div>
    <div class="prl-symptom-item"><span class="prl-symptom-check">✔</span><span>Lie in bed wondering if your lungs will ever feel normal again.</span></div>
  </div>

  <p>It's not in your head. It's not "just getting older."</p>

  <p><strong>Your lungs are still buried under years of damage, with no support to recover.</strong></p>

  <div class="prl-divider"></div>

  <!-- ═══ SECTION 4: WHY NOTHING ELSE HAS WORKED ═══ -->
  <div class="prl-section-label-wrap">
    <span class="prl-section-badge">03</span>
    <span class="prl-section-label-text">Why Nothing Else Has Worked</span>
  </div>

  <p>I spent years watching my patients try everything.</p>

  <p>Over-the-counter expectorants that masked the cough for a few hours and did nothing about the underlying buildup.</p>

  <p>Supplements packed with 15 different ingredients at doses too low to matter, designed by marketing teams and not pharmacists.</p>

  <p>Breathing exercises and steam inhalation that felt nice in the moment but didn't move the needle.</p>

  <p>And the most common advice of all, the one I got so sick of hearing that it's practically burned into my brain:</p>

  <div class="prl-pull-quote">"Just give it time."</div>

  <p>Time. That's what they told my grandma. That's what they told my aunts.</p>

  <p>I watched three people run out of time.</p>

  <p><strong>I was done waiting.</strong></p>

